WEBVTT

00:00.793 --> 00:02.419
[♪ opening theme song playing]

00:34.368 --> 00:38.497
JUJUTSU KAISEN

01:30.758 --> 01:32.843
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

01:36.388 --> 01:38.807
[footsteps receding]

01:56.742 --> 01:59.870
EPISODE 49
ONE MORE TIME

02:00.203 --> 02:01.455
[YUTA] I'm sorry.

02:02.706 --> 02:04.249
- [squelching]
- Itadori.

02:07.878 --> 02:09.004
[Sukuna scoffs]

02:14.384 --> 02:16.219
[♪ dramatic music playing]

02:19.723 --> 02:20.808
[grunts]

02:22.225 --> 02:25.479
[grunting]

02:26.939 --> 02:28.565
[groans, grunts]

02:29.441 --> 02:30.651
[grunts]

02:37.365 --> 02:38.450
[scoffs]

02:42.161 --> 02:43.538
[CHOSO] He's fast.

02:43.580 --> 02:45.373
I can't figure out
the trick to his technique.

02:45.415 --> 02:47.459
With him
overwhelmingly me this badly,

02:47.501 --> 02:49.795
he's not likely to
reveal his hand.

02:49.837 --> 02:52.422
I have no chance
to use Convergence.

02:53.298 --> 02:56.760
None of my external
Blood Manipulation is usable.

03:06.436 --> 03:07.855
You're persistent.

03:07.896 --> 03:09.690
Seriously, though, what are you?

03:10.357 --> 03:14.069
An older brother
with nine younger siblings.

03:14.444 --> 03:17.072
Flowing Red Scale - Stack!

03:17.114 --> 03:19.867
[NAOYA] Good to know,
but that's not what I asked.

03:19.908 --> 03:21.952
I wanna know
why you're so tough,

03:22.369 --> 03:24.746
and about that technique
of yours. [grunts]

03:31.170 --> 03:32.504
[whooshes]

03:42.430 --> 03:44.391
He's starting to match me.

03:46.267 --> 03:47.811
[thuds]

03:49.563 --> 03:50.605
[Choso gasps]

03:52.066 --> 03:53.901
[NAOYA] I see what he's up to.

03:53.942 --> 03:55.986
Flowing Red Scale, huh?

03:56.361 --> 03:58.780
He's focusing that power
on his external eye muscles

03:58.822 --> 04:00.741
to improve his kinetic vision.

04:01.909 --> 04:03.577
You can't beat me.

04:03.618 --> 04:07.081
I can counter your moves before
you even know you'll make them.

04:07.122 --> 04:08.582
Since you're so persistent,

04:08.623 --> 04:10.458
I went ahead and used my weapon.

04:10.500 --> 04:12.127
Don't worry.

04:12.169 --> 04:14.922
You can easily stop the bleeding
with your Blood Manipulation.

04:15.380 --> 04:17.841
But let's find out
how well you do fighting me

04:17.883 --> 04:19.968
and staunching your blood
at the same time.

04:20.010 --> 04:21.553
[CHOSO] You came
prepared with a sword.

04:21.595 --> 04:23.638
[NAOYA] Keep it a secret,
will ya?

04:23.680 --> 04:25.099
Honestly, I think it's lame,

04:25.140 --> 04:27.392
a sorcerer walking around
with a weapon?

04:27.434 --> 04:29.477
Feels strange if
you can't win without it.

04:29.519 --> 04:31.772
But a surprising number
of people think this way.

04:31.813 --> 04:32.981
It's not just me.

04:33.607 --> 04:35.817
I mean, I think
my older brothers are pathetic

04:35.859 --> 04:37.152
for carrying them,

04:37.194 --> 04:38.904
and yet they think
they have some kind of right

04:38.946 --> 04:40.572
to complain about Toji.

04:40.614 --> 04:41.949
You hate them, don't you?

04:41.990 --> 04:43.575
Your older brothers?

04:43.617 --> 04:44.993
I do hate them.

04:45.035 --> 04:46.995
Older brothers less competent
than younger brothers

04:47.037 --> 04:48.371
serve no purpose.

04:48.413 --> 04:50.958
Actually, I think they
deserve to be hanged.

04:50.999 --> 04:53.001
You should have gratitude
towards them.

04:53.460 --> 04:56.421
Your older brothers have
shaped who you are today.

04:56.463 --> 04:57.881
Ugh.

04:57.923 --> 05:01.135
That is the most disgusting
thing I have ever heard.

05:01.176 --> 05:02.761
Please don't gross me out.

05:03.971 --> 05:06.389
Whether or not
older brothers are competent,

05:06.431 --> 05:08.976
they set an example
for their younger brothers.

05:09.017 --> 05:11.228
If I make mistakes
and go down the wrong path,

05:11.270 --> 05:13.647
then my little brothers
can avoid that path.

05:13.897 --> 05:15.857
And if I go down
the proper path,

05:15.899 --> 05:18.819
then my little brothers
can follow after me.

05:18.860 --> 05:20.403
What would you do

05:20.445 --> 05:23.782
if you were strong because
your older brothers proved weak?

05:24.158 --> 05:26.743
- You asked me why I'm tough?
- Hmm?

05:26.785 --> 05:27.869
[CHOSO] I'll tell you.

05:28.369 --> 05:29.871
I never had an example.

05:29.913 --> 05:32.415
I had to make many,
many mistakes.

05:32.457 --> 05:33.750
And yet,

05:33.792 --> 05:36.461
I kept walking in front
of my younger brothers.

05:36.503 --> 05:38.297
And that made me strong!

05:38.337 --> 05:39.756
[♪ dramatic music playing]

05:42.717 --> 05:44.469
[NAOYA]
What's he going on about?

05:44.511 --> 05:47.306
And how is he still alive
after bleeding so much?

05:55.022 --> 05:58.357
[NARRATOR] The Death Paintings
are a mix of curse and human.

05:58.399 --> 06:00.027
They possess the unique ability

06:00.068 --> 06:02.403
to convert
cursed energy into blood.

06:02.654 --> 06:05.115
Until their cursed energy
dries up,

06:05.157 --> 06:07.701
they cannot die
from blood loss.

06:14.916 --> 06:15.959
[groans]

06:31.850 --> 06:33.977
[light switch thudding]

06:34.019 --> 06:35.645
[NAOYA] Why are my legs heavy?

06:36.521 --> 06:37.689
Did he harden the blood

06:37.731 --> 06:39.566
that seeped into
the fabric of my shoes?

06:39.607 --> 06:41.526
[CHOSO] Do you understand now?

06:42.569 --> 06:44.154
This is checkmate.

06:50.202 --> 06:52.204
Don't congratulate yourself yet.

06:53.330 --> 06:55.957
My technique traces
my opponent's future motions

06:55.999 --> 06:57.834
at 24 frames per second.

06:58.335 --> 07:00.170
This is only a minor hindrance.

07:00.212 --> 07:01.755
I can still move.

07:02.797 --> 07:04.132
He missed his chance.

07:07.719 --> 07:09.930
Why isn't he
striking out against me?

07:10.513 --> 07:12.473
[NARRATOR] Developed after
grappling with his technique

07:12.515 --> 07:14.768
for over 150 years,

07:14.809 --> 07:16.561
this was a Choso original.

07:16.603 --> 07:17.562
SUPERNOVA

07:17.604 --> 07:18.646
[explosions]

07:18.688 --> 07:19.689
[grunts]

07:27.364 --> 07:29.199
[Naoya gasping]

07:29.241 --> 07:32.035
[choking, breathing raggedly]

07:42.837 --> 07:44.339
I'm sorry,

07:44.381 --> 07:47.801
but I can't understand how
you never loved your brothers.

07:55.642 --> 07:57.769
[footsteps approaching]

07:57.811 --> 07:58.812
[gasps]

08:02.774 --> 08:04.234
- [gasps]
- [punches]

08:09.906 --> 08:11.616
[YUTA] That looks painful.

08:13.243 --> 08:14.369
Naoya.

08:16.788 --> 08:18.539
[hisses]

08:18.581 --> 08:20.375
[NAOYA] Don't look down on me.

08:20.417 --> 08:21.542
[gasps]

08:21.584 --> 08:25.213
[choking, retching]

08:27.424 --> 08:29.301
[NAOYA] What is this? Poison?

08:29.343 --> 08:30.760
[groaning]

08:30.802 --> 08:32.262
Blood Manipulation
shouldn't be capable of...

08:32.304 --> 08:35.349
No, it's not
a product of his technique.

08:35.723 --> 08:40.145
He had that much blood
because he's not human!

08:40.187 --> 08:41.938
Could it be an incarnation?

08:42.272 --> 08:44.858
Is his inhuman blood
in my body being rejected?

08:44.899 --> 08:46.276
[YUTA] Shall I heal you?

08:47.486 --> 08:49.570
I have reverse cursed technique.

08:49.612 --> 08:51.530
It can heal people.

08:51.572 --> 08:53.116
And then in return,

08:53.532 --> 08:55.660
could you please
report Itadori's death

08:55.702 --> 08:58.788
to the top brass,
as per our arrangement?

09:01.500 --> 09:03.043
[YUJI'S GRANDFATHER]
Jin! [echoing]

09:09.174 --> 09:10.842
Yes, Father. What is it?

09:11.218 --> 09:12.886
But if you wanna
talk about her again,

09:12.927 --> 09:14.012
then I'm going home.

09:14.846 --> 09:17.516
Look, Jin,
you're free to live your life

09:17.556 --> 09:19.476
whichever way you choose.

09:20.143 --> 09:23.562
However, you have to
stay away from that woman,

09:23.604 --> 09:24.981
or you'll die!

09:25.690 --> 09:27.401
Please stop saying
such terrible things

09:27.442 --> 09:29.027
in front of Yuji, Father.

09:29.568 --> 09:32.280
You'd be surprised at how much
a baby can remember.

09:32.739 --> 09:34.741
I know that the most
important thing for you

09:34.782 --> 09:35.992
was to have a child.

09:36.034 --> 09:37.702
And I'm sorry
that you were never able

09:37.744 --> 09:39.079
to do that with Kaori.

09:39.120 --> 09:42.499
But, son, Kaori died
and you know I'm-- [gasps]

09:42.541 --> 09:44.042
Now, Father,

09:44.084 --> 09:45.544
why would you say that?

09:47.087 --> 09:49.256
[fire crackling]

09:50.715 --> 09:51.966
[gasps]

09:58.473 --> 09:59.474
[grunts]

09:59.516 --> 10:01.600
I'm alive. But how?

10:18.701 --> 10:20.036
[Yuta sighs]

10:20.619 --> 10:23.831
Oh, thank goodness! [laughs]

10:24.374 --> 10:25.459
[gasps]

10:26.960 --> 10:28.836
[chuckling]

10:28.878 --> 10:29.879
[sighs]

10:30.505 --> 10:32.173
It was September, I think.

10:32.966 --> 10:35.760
Satoru Gojo went out of his way
to see me.

10:36.219 --> 10:38.472
He asked me
to always watch after you.

10:38.846 --> 10:41.266
[chuckles] So I had no choice

10:41.308 --> 10:43.143
but to put on that act.

10:43.184 --> 10:44.561
You were acting?

10:45.103 --> 10:48.356
[SATORU] I've got
a bit of a bad feeling.

10:48.398 --> 10:49.983
If anything happens to me,

10:50.024 --> 10:51.485
I want you
to take care of the first

10:51.526 --> 10:52.902
and second-year students.

10:53.320 --> 10:55.614
Except for Hakari.
He'll be fine.

10:56.406 --> 10:57.824
If anything happens?

10:58.116 --> 10:59.534
You in trouble with a woman?

11:00.659 --> 11:02.036
[SATORU] I'm glad to see
you've developed

11:02.078 --> 11:03.788
a sense of humor, Yuta.

11:03.830 --> 11:05.624
[Yuta chuckles] No, I'm serious.

11:05.664 --> 11:09.169
I just can't imagine
anything happening to you, Gojo.

11:09.210 --> 11:10.669
[SATORU] Well, just in case,

11:10.711 --> 11:12.671
take special care
of Yuji Itadori.

11:12.713 --> 11:15.509
He's been sentenced to
secret execution, like you were.

11:15.550 --> 11:18.178
It would be a big help to me
if you looked out for him.

11:19.513 --> 11:21.389
Oh, by the way, how's Miguel?

11:21.431 --> 11:23.141
He said he didn't wanna see you.

11:23.558 --> 11:24.643
Eh?

11:25.684 --> 11:27.437
[YUTA]
This act was the best option

11:27.479 --> 11:30.273
to prevent someone else
from being sent to execute you.

11:30.731 --> 11:33.901
And to cut off any information
about you to others as well.

11:34.528 --> 11:36.863
Then again,
they're not idiots either.

11:37.238 --> 11:39.991
So before they would
approve me as the executioner,

11:40.033 --> 11:43.036
headquarters made me forge
a pact to make sure I did it.

11:43.662 --> 11:46.873
That's the reason I actually
had to kill you for a moment.

11:46.914 --> 11:48.500
I'm real sorry about that.

11:49.250 --> 11:53.129
Wait. If you killed me,
then how am I still alive?

11:53.712 --> 11:55.507
Reverse cursed technique.

11:56.090 --> 11:57.676
I used my reverse
cursed technique

11:57.716 --> 12:00.803
the moment your heart stopped
to immediately heal you.

12:01.179 --> 12:02.681
I figured it would work,

12:02.721 --> 12:04.807
based upon all the things
I've heard about you before.

12:04.849 --> 12:06.184
I guess I was right.

12:06.560 --> 12:08.144
There aren't
too many people around

12:08.186 --> 12:12.190
who know that I'm capable
of outputting positive energy.

12:12.232 --> 12:15.068
This is the second time
you faked your death.

12:15.569 --> 12:17.195
They're bound to figure it out.

12:17.736 --> 12:19.614
But the situation's
still chaotic.

12:19.656 --> 12:21.199
They're going to believe
you're dead,

12:21.241 --> 12:22.867
for a while at least.

12:22.909 --> 12:23.910
Headquarters will think

12:23.951 --> 12:26.120
your death sentence
was carried out.

12:28.623 --> 12:30.041
Why go this far?

12:30.083 --> 12:31.792
What's in it for you?

12:31.834 --> 12:34.588
I'm doing it because
the people that I cherish

12:35.255 --> 12:37.756
also happen to be
people who cherish you.

12:39.926 --> 12:41.802
The power I shoulder,

12:41.844 --> 12:44.389
I used to think it was greater
than I could bear.

12:44.763 --> 12:48.059
At first, I'd thought the power
had been forced upon me,

12:48.101 --> 12:51.730
but it was really something
that I'd brought upon myself.

12:52.355 --> 12:55.233
I'm not like you. The power
you shoulder isn't yours.

12:58.319 --> 13:00.029
It's not your fault.

13:06.035 --> 13:07.245
That's not true.

13:07.287 --> 13:08.496
You don't get it.

13:08.538 --> 13:10.707
It isn't a matter of
who's to blame or not.

13:10.749 --> 13:11.874
I killed them.

13:11.916 --> 13:13.460
- It was me--
- [MEGUMI] Itadori.

13:13.501 --> 13:14.919
[gasps]

13:18.214 --> 13:20.799
[gasps] Fushiguro,
what are you doing here?

13:20.841 --> 13:22.719
We're going back
to Jujutsu High.

13:23.094 --> 13:25.639
The barrier surrounding
the school has been weakened.

13:25.680 --> 13:28.015
It should be safe
for you to return there again.

13:28.057 --> 13:29.726
So long as no one
sees your face.

13:30.268 --> 13:31.810
We'll meet up with
the upperclassmen and then--

13:31.852 --> 13:32.895
Stop it!

13:33.605 --> 13:37.066
Don't talk about it like
it's just another normal day.

13:37.734 --> 13:39.818
Don't just pretend
it didn't happen.

13:41.279 --> 13:42.739
I killed people.

13:43.239 --> 13:44.574
A lot of people.

13:45.950 --> 13:47.952
It's because of me
that so many are dead now!

13:47.994 --> 13:49.287
[MEGUMI] Because of us!

13:50.538 --> 13:52.332
[YUJI] Of course
you would say that.

13:53.082 --> 13:54.751
[MEGUMI] You can't give up

13:55.251 --> 13:56.795
just because you want to.

14:04.803 --> 14:05.804
[sighs]

14:10.517 --> 14:11.934
We aren't heroes.

14:12.393 --> 14:13.812
We're jujutsu sorcerers.

14:14.688 --> 14:17.273
There's no one who can
judge us unless they've been us.

14:17.856 --> 14:19.317
That's all the more reason

14:20.067 --> 14:22.779
why we have to
keep proving why we exist.

14:24.781 --> 14:26.741
[YUJI] You're wrong, Fushiguro.

14:26.783 --> 14:28.618
We don't have time
to worry about ourselves

14:28.660 --> 14:30.119
and our feelings anymore.

14:30.161 --> 14:33.122
- [YUJI] Don't say that or...
- We exist to save others.

14:33.581 --> 14:34.999
[YUJI]
...you'll end up suffering...

14:35.041 --> 14:37.418
I thought saving people
was your driving motivation.

14:37.752 --> 14:39.212
[YUJI]...the whole time
you stay around me.

14:39.253 --> 14:41.673
Start by saving me, Itadori.

14:45.051 --> 14:46.093
[gasps]

14:46.135 --> 14:48.429
Noritoshi Kamo has
set up a death game

14:48.471 --> 14:51.265
between those he granted
cursed techniques.

14:51.307 --> 14:52.266
The Culling Game.

14:52.308 --> 14:53.852
[♪ sentimental music playing]

14:55.144 --> 14:57.605
Tsumiki has been drawn
into this game, too.

14:59.399 --> 15:00.483
Itadori...

15:01.192 --> 15:02.276
please.

15:07.948 --> 15:09.701
I need your power.

15:17.834 --> 15:22.422
THE CULLING GAME
GENERAL RULES

15:22.463 --> 15:23.381
THE CULLING GAME
GENERAL RULES

15:23.423 --> 15:24.507
WITHIN 19 DAYS
PARTICIPATE

15:25.132 --> 15:26.175
BREACH
TECHNIQUE- STRIPPED

15:26.801 --> 15:27.926
ENTERING A COLONY
PARTICIPATE

15:28.803 --> 15:29.846
ENDING
THE LIFE

15:30.430 --> 15:31.472
SORCERER 5 POINTS

15:31.514 --> 15:32.557
NON-SORCERER 1 POINT

15:40.939 --> 15:42.983
JUJUTSU KAISEN

15:50.074 --> 15:51.659
Okkotsu, I need your help.

15:52.410 --> 15:55.204
Sukuna's plotting something
that uses Fushiguro.

15:55.996 --> 15:58.499
He was able
to take over my body in Shibuya

15:58.541 --> 16:01.043
after I was forced
to eat 10 fingers at once.

16:01.795 --> 16:04.464
There's now a total
of 15 fingers inside of me.

16:04.839 --> 16:07.341
Even if I'm fed
the remaining five all at once,

16:07.383 --> 16:09.968
I don't think he'll be able
to take me over again.

16:10.010 --> 16:11.178
But if he does,

16:11.554 --> 16:14.181
if Sukuna appears
and takes control of me again,

16:14.223 --> 16:16.726
I need you to kill me.

16:16.768 --> 16:18.603
Can I trust you
to do that for me?

16:20.271 --> 16:21.564
Yes, of course.

16:22.356 --> 16:24.024
I promise I'll do it.

16:24.692 --> 16:25.944
Okay, Fushiguro.

16:26.402 --> 16:27.946
What do you need me to do?

16:28.696 --> 16:30.615
First, we go back
to Jujutsu High

16:30.657 --> 16:32.575
and then make
contact with Tengen.

16:35.536 --> 16:37.914
How can we release
the seal of the Prison Realm?

16:38.247 --> 16:40.667
What is Noritoshi Kamo's
actual goal?

16:40.708 --> 16:42.209
And what moves will he make?

16:43.001 --> 16:44.587
The Culling Game
is an unprecedented act

16:44.629 --> 16:46.255
of jujutsu terrorism,

16:46.297 --> 16:47.799
and we need answers
to those questions

16:47.841 --> 16:49.300
to resolve this situation.

16:49.926 --> 16:51.594
I think the Tengen
might be the only one

16:51.636 --> 16:53.680
capable of answering them.

16:53.721 --> 16:55.222
[YUJI] What about that woman?

16:55.264 --> 16:56.641
Maybe Tsukumo knows.

16:57.057 --> 16:59.352
[MEGUMI]
I've already spoken to Tsukumo.

16:59.393 --> 17:01.479
In fact,
this whole thing was her plan.

17:01.813 --> 17:04.190
She's also hiding away
at Jujutsu High.

17:06.024 --> 17:07.861
Hiding away from what?

17:08.569 --> 17:10.697
Apparently, she doesn't
wanna deal with the higher-ups.

17:11.155 --> 17:14.993
However, the problem is
Tengen's concealment barriers.

17:15.702 --> 17:17.119
Within the barriers,

17:17.161 --> 17:19.873
there are a thousand
constantly shuffling doors.

17:19.914 --> 17:22.625
Only one leads to
the Tombs of the Star

17:22.667 --> 17:24.210
where Tengen resides.

17:25.378 --> 17:27.338
[YUJI] So unless
we pick the right door,

17:27.755 --> 17:29.382
we can't meet with Tengen?

17:34.345 --> 17:36.347
I'm sorry, Fushiguro, but...

17:45.231 --> 17:46.816
I need to ask you something.

17:50.862 --> 17:52.655
What happened to Kugisaki?

17:59.996 --> 18:01.039
I see.

18:04.417 --> 18:05.418
All right.

18:05.459 --> 18:06.502
[sobs]

18:13.300 --> 18:15.177
All right, I... I understand.

18:16.429 --> 18:18.639
So, about
the concealment barriers.

18:19.057 --> 18:20.975
I have a good workaround
for that.

18:21.017 --> 18:23.019
[YUTA] How long
has he been listening?

18:25.312 --> 18:27.231
What's the workaround? Tell us.

18:27.815 --> 18:30.526
You remember when
Mahito stole Sukuna's fingers

18:30.568 --> 18:32.028
and the Death Paintings?

18:32.737 --> 18:34.906
We're going to do
the same thing.

18:40.954 --> 18:43.915
[indistinct chatter on TV]

18:43.957 --> 18:46.960
Well, it hasn't been that long
since the last time, huh?

18:47.001 --> 18:48.461
Maki, what a surprise.

18:49.587 --> 18:50.838
Oh, hello.

18:51.380 --> 18:54.550
Maki! Is it safe
for you to be up?

18:54.592 --> 18:57.011
Yeah, it's not a problem.

18:57.053 --> 18:59.179
Not much I could do
about the burns.

18:59.221 --> 19:01.641
Reverse cursed technique
can't erase scars.

19:01.682 --> 19:03.309
I have to say,
your Heavenly Pact

19:03.350 --> 19:05.603
of physical prowess
is impressive.

19:05.645 --> 19:07.229
You saved your life
with the strength

19:07.271 --> 19:08.606
of your body's endurance.

19:08.648 --> 19:10.566
You didn't put faith
in your resistance

19:10.608 --> 19:11.943
to curses alone.

19:11.985 --> 19:14.070
It's a shame
the clan head didn't make it.

19:14.112 --> 19:16.697
[MAKI] It's not like it was
a competition or something.

19:18.074 --> 19:20.576
Megumi, how's it going
with Tengen's barrier?

19:22.286 --> 19:23.746
Well, you see--

19:23.788 --> 19:25.123
Let me explain.

19:25.163 --> 19:27.291
On the way
to the Tombs of the Star

19:27.333 --> 19:28.793
is the forbidden vault.

19:28.835 --> 19:31.378
Inside that vault are
Jujutsu High's cursed tools

19:31.420 --> 19:32.922
and cursed objects.

19:32.964 --> 19:34.966
Plus, the remains
of my brothers.

19:35.299 --> 19:41.221
Noranso, Sho-oso, Tanso,
Sanso, Kotsuso, and Shoso.

19:41.263 --> 19:43.099
Even though
it's just their remains,

19:43.141 --> 19:44.684
I should be able
to sense their presence

19:44.725 --> 19:46.853
using the side effect
of my technique.

19:48.604 --> 19:49.814
Good for you!

19:50.188 --> 19:51.983
That's really great to hear.

19:52.025 --> 19:53.442
But who are you?

19:56.946 --> 19:58.656
Well, for now...

19:59.448 --> 20:01.784
I guess you can call him
my older brother.

20:01.826 --> 20:05.163
[yelling emotionally] Yuji!

20:05.203 --> 20:06.413
[YUJI] Let's go.

20:09.167 --> 20:10.459
[CHOSO] That's the one.

20:10.501 --> 20:12.003
I'm certain of it.

20:12.045 --> 20:15.173
My younger brothers are
resting right beyond this door.

20:15.213 --> 20:16.423
I'm opening it.

20:26.893 --> 20:28.226
[YUKI] Let's head down.

20:29.812 --> 20:31.229
Further in, there's an elevator

20:31.271 --> 20:33.191
leading to
the Tombs of the Star.

20:34.400 --> 20:35.526
[YUJI] Choso.

20:36.527 --> 20:38.445
[CHOSO] Coming.

20:38.487 --> 20:40.156
I'll come back for you later.

20:40.489 --> 20:42.200
Hang in there a little longer.

20:43.701 --> 20:45.536
[mechanical whirring]

20:45.578 --> 20:47.121
[door opens]

20:48.915 --> 20:50.124
[YUJI] Bloodstains?

20:50.166 --> 20:51.584
I wonder what happened.

20:51.625 --> 20:53.794
[YUKI] It was 12 years ago.

20:53.836 --> 20:55.129
Thinking back on it now,

20:55.171 --> 20:57.423
that's when
all the distortions started.

20:57.464 --> 21:00.927
Can't just be
a coincidence, can it?

21:00.968 --> 21:03.804
All right, everyone,
the main hall is just up ahead.

21:17.902 --> 21:18.861
[gasps]

21:18.903 --> 21:20.529
[YUJI] There's nothing here.

21:20.571 --> 21:22.031
This is the main hall?

21:22.489 --> 21:25.159
[YUKI] No,
he's declining to speak with us.

21:25.534 --> 21:28.162
Tengen won't interfere
with reality.

21:28.204 --> 21:30.456
I thought if there was
ever a chance to reach him,

21:30.497 --> 21:31.582
it would be now,

21:31.624 --> 21:33.667
while the Six Eyes
are sealed away.

21:34.001 --> 21:35.753
I was obviously naive.

21:37.046 --> 21:39.799
It's not all of us
being rejected,

21:39.840 --> 21:42.009
but just me?

21:44.678 --> 21:46.097
We should head back.

21:46.430 --> 21:48.557
Tsumiki doesn't
have time to spare.

21:50.726 --> 21:52.979
[TENGEN] Leaving so soon?

21:53.437 --> 21:56.232
It's nice to meet you,
Child of Zen'in.

21:56.274 --> 21:58.316
Descendant of Michizane,

21:58.358 --> 22:00.360
Cursed Womb Death Painting,

22:00.402 --> 22:01.737
and at last...

22:03.530 --> 22:05.365
it's the Vessel of Sukuna.

22:10.328 --> 22:12.498
[♪ closing theme song playing]

23:39.877 --> 23:41.795
[TENGEN]
I must impose one condition.

23:41.837 --> 23:43.839
[YUTA] We came here to learn
how to open the Prison Realm.

23:43.881 --> 23:44.965
[YUKI] No greeting for me?

23:45.007 --> 23:46.550
[MEGUMI]
Then why is this Culling Game?

23:46.592 --> 23:48.386
[TENGEN] To force
the evolution of mankind.

23:48.426 --> 23:49.970
[SHOKO] It's better
for the rules if being stripped

23:50.012 --> 23:51.097
means death, too.

23:51.138 --> 23:52.139
[YUJI] If Sukuna
takes control again,

23:52.181 --> 23:53.266
don't hesitate to kill me.

23:53.307 --> 23:54.392
[CHOSO] Don't die out there.
